trans-unit.source: Contains a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
ASP.NET health monitoring allows production and operations staff to manage deployed Web applications.
The <xref:System.Web.Management> namespace contains the health event types responsible for packaging application health-status data and the provider types responsible for processing this data.
It also contains supporting types that help during the management of health events.
The WebBaseEventCollection class is used to deliver a collection of health-monitoring events to providers such as the <xref:System.Web.Management.SqlWebEventProvider>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEventCollection"></xref> class.

The WebBaseEventCollection constructor allows you to create an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Management.WebBaseEventCollection> class and initialize it with a collection of <xref:System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent> objects.
The collection of <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent"></xref> objects.
